Here's a basic example of an HTML form for user registration that includes fields for personal information like name, address, and email:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>User Registration Form</title>
    <style>
        /* Basic styling for the form */
        form {
            width: 50%;
            margin: 40px auto;
            padding: 20px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            border-radius: 10px;
            box-shadow: 0 0 10px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1);
        }

        label {
            display: block;
            margin-bottom: 10px;
        }

        input, select, textarea {
            width: 100%;
            height: 40px;
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
        }

        button[type="submit"] {
            background-color: #4CAF50;
            color: #fff;
            padding: 10px 20px;
            border: none;
            border-radius: 5px;
            cursor: pointer;
        }

        button[type="submit"]:hover {
            background-color: #3e8e41;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <h2>User Registration Form</h2>
    <form action="register.php" method="post">
        <label for="name">Name:</label>
        <input type="text" id="name" name="name" required>

        <label for="email">Email:</label>
        <input type="email" id="email" name="email" required>

        <label for="address">Address:</label>
        <textarea id="address" name="address" required></textarea>

        <label for="city">City:</label>
        <input type="text" id="city" name="city" required>

        <label for="state">State:</label>
        <input type="text" id="state" name="state" required>

        <label for="zip">Zip:</label>
        <input type="text" id="zip" name="zip" required>

        <button type="submit">Register</button>
    </form>
</body>
</html>
```

This form includes the following fields:

*   **Name:** A text input field for the user's name.
*   **Email:** An email input field for the user's email address.
*   **Address:** A textarea field for the user's address.
*   **City:** A text input field for the user's city.
*   **State:** A text input field for the user's state.
*   **Zip:** A text input field for the user's zip code.

The form also includes a submit button to send the form data to the server for processing.

Note that this is a basic example, and you should consider adding additional validation and security measures to your form to ensure that user data is collected and processed securely.

Also, the form action attribute points to a PHP file (`register.php`) which is not included in this example. You would need to create this file to process the form data and store it in a database or perform any other necessary actions.

